---
import BlogPostLayout from '@layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';
import Picture from '@components/ui/Picture.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'From how many people is it considered a group?',
    a: '<p>In practice, from <strong>8 people</strong> we already talk about a group, because it involves coordinating canoes, schedules and transfer. From 15 people we treat it as a group booking with a single contact and margin to customise the picnic, time and stops. No strict minimum: in 25 years we have organised everything from couples to coaches of 60 people.</p>',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do you do Sella descents for stag or hen parties?',
    a: '<p>Yes. Stag/hen parties are <strong>one of our favourite plans</strong> — good vibes, laughs and the Sella takes care of the rest. Since the schedule is <strong>Premium · open hours</strong>, you arrive at the facilities <strong>between 10:30 and 12:30</strong> · no fixed time. If you want the calmer river feel, arrive early (10:30-11:00) · if you prefer a lively midday, arrive around 12:00. Remember to book in advance (August fills up fast) and that <strong>no alcohol is consumed on the river</strong> — leave it for the post-descent meal.</p>',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can the descent be booked exclusively for a group?',
    a: '<p>The river is public, so <strong>it cannot be "privatised"</strong>. We can reserve a specific time slot so the whole group launches together, with <strong>explanatory class adapted to the group size</strong>, certified instructors watching the river during the day and special treatment at reception. If you are a very large group (30+), write to us and we will see how to organise it.</p>',
  },
  {
    q: 'What do we do if some of the group do not want to paddle?',
    a: '<p>It is common: in almost every stag/hen or family event there is someone who prefers not to paddle. Arriondas has <strong>cafés, a square and a riverside walk</strong> for them to wait calmly, and they can join the group at the final snack bar. Those who paddle pay normal price, those who do not, do not pay.</p>',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is there a group discount?',
    a: '<p>It depends on volume. From <strong>15-20 people</strong> we can consider special terms. Write to the <a href="/en/contact/">contact form</a> with exact number of people, preferred date and ages (to separate kids/adults) and we will send a closed quote.</p>',
  },
  {
    q: 'What clothes do you recommend for groups?',
    a: '<p>The same list as for any descent — we have it in full at <a href="/en/blog/what-to-bring-sella-descent/">what to bring for the Sella descent</a>. A specific group tip: <strong>matching colour or slogan t-shirts</strong> look great in photos from the river. Many hen parties do it and the images are spectacular.</p>',
  },
];
---

<BlogPostLayout slug="sella-descent-groups-stag-do" faqs={faqs}>
  <p class="post__intro">
    <strong>Coverage:</strong> stag and hen parties, birthdays, silver weddings, friend gatherings, companies with real <em>team building</em>, big families, friend crews. If you thought the Sella descent was only for 2 people in a canoe, here we explain how it is organised when there are 8, 20 or 50 of you.
  </p>

  <p>
    In the last 25 years we have seen everything on the Sella: hen parties with costumes, weddings that complete the weekend with the descent on Saturday, companies measuring team cohesion on the river, crews who have been paddling together since they were 18. The river adapts well to groups — you just need to organise it with a bit of head.
  </p>

  <p>
    This guide explains how we approach the descent in groups, what advantages it has, what to think about in advance and what questions always come up in group bookings.
  </p>

  <h2 class="post__h2" id="why-sella">Why <span class="serif-italic">the Sella works</span> for groups</h2>

  <p>Six reasons stag/hen parties, companies and big families come back to the Sella year after year.</p>

  <div class="post__essentials">
    <article class="post__essential">
