  </div>

  <figure class="post__figure">
    <Picture
      src="blog-grupos-inline"
      alt="Group of friends on a hen party paddling the Sella River in a canoe — the plan that fits big crews"
      sizes="(min-width: 1024px) 680px, 92vw"
      aspectRatio="16 / 10"
    />
    <figcaption>Crews, hen/stag parties, company teams, big families. The Sella adapts to the group · you just need to organise the morning with head.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h2 class="post__h2" id="stag-hen">Stag <span class="serif-italic">and hen parties</span></h2>

  <p>
    If there is one type of group that asks for the Sella again and again, it is stag/hen parties. And rightly: it is a full outdoor day plan, compatible with mixed ages (grandma, cousin, friend from work), with photos for the bride or groom, and an atmosphere that does not tire.
  </p>

  <h3 class="post__h3">The typical recipe for a hen party on the Sella</h3>

  <ol class="post__timeline">
    <li>
      <time>10:30</time>
      <div class="post__timeline__body"><strong>Arrival in Arriondas.</strong> Registration, changing rooms, costumes if you brought them (they fit in the locked lockers).</div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <time>10:50</time>
      <div class="post__timeline__body"><strong>Mini-class.</strong> Ten minutes · used for the first jokes and a photo before going down to the river.</div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <time>11:30</time>
      <div class="post__timeline__body"><strong>Launch.</strong> Mandatory group photo from the ramp before starting.</div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <time>12:30</time>
      <div class="post__timeline__body"><strong>Stop at <a href="/en/blog/pozo-del-arco-sella/">Pozo del Arco</a>.</strong> Swim, group photo, Asturian picnic at a good hour if you fancy.</div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <time>13:30</time>
      <div class="post__timeline__body"><strong>Stop at a <a href="/en/blog/sella-descent-riverside-bars/">snack bar on the route</a>.</strong> Drink, music, laughs · usually El Oasis or El Bosque. <em>No alcohol on the river · leave it for after.</em></div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <time>14:30</time>
      <div class="post__timeline__body"><strong>Arrival at Toraño or Fríes.</strong> Return transfer to Arriondas.</div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <time>15:00</time>
      <div class="post__timeline__body"><strong>Showers and change.</strong> At the facilities · hot water and changing rooms included.</div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <time>16:00</time>
      <div class="post__timeline__body"><strong>Post-descent meal.</strong> Cider house in Arriondas, Cangas or Ribadesella · we recommend places if you ask.</div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <div class="post__callout">
    <strong>House tips for stag/hen parties</strong>
    <ul class="post__callout__items">
      <li>Book <strong>2-3 weeks ahead in August</strong> · Saturdays fill up fast.</li>
      <li><strong>Matching-colour t-shirts</strong> for the whole group · memorable photos from the river.</li>
      <li><strong>No alcohol on the river.</strong> It is prohibited by regulation and the snack bars do not serve it · leave it for the post-descent meal.</li>
      <li>Be careful with <strong>bulky costumes</strong> in the canoe · they should be comfortable and able to get wet.</li>
      <li>Let us know if anyone is <strong>pregnant</strong> · they cannot paddle, but they can wait in Arriondas without trouble.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 class="post__h2" id="companies">Companies and <span class="serif-italic">team building</span></h2>

  <p>
    The Sella works well as a company activity because <strong>it has no physical entry barrier</strong> (nobody is left out for not being in shape), it generates conversation between colleagues who normally do not interact, and it leaves a shared memory that lasts months.
  </p>

  <p>For companies we usually offer:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dedicated time slot</strong> — the whole group launches together.</li>
    <li><strong>Certified instructors</strong> on the river watching the route (briefing class beforehand + safety kayaks during the day).</li>
    <li><strong>Asturian picnic</strong> reinforced if it is a long event — pie, traditional bun, cheese, extra fruit.</li>
    <li><strong>Tax invoice</strong> to the company's tax ID.</li>
    <li><strong>Coordination with local accommodation or catering</strong> if needed.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    The typical company plan is early arrival on Premium open hours (10:30-11:00), <a href="/en/how-long-does-it-take/">Full route descent</a>, post-meal at a cider house near Arriondas or Cangas. With 30-40 people it is comfortably organised. If you are 60+, let's talk and we will see how.
  </p>

  <h2 class="post__h2" id="families">Birthdays, families and <span class="serif-italic">big gatherings</span></h2>

  <p>
    Birthdays (especially <strong>40, 50, 60</strong>) and anniversaries are another classic. The key here is that in a family group there are very mixed ages — from 8-year-old cousins to 75-year-old grandparents. The Sella descent handles it well because:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Canoes up to 3 seats (K3)</strong> allow combinations of couples + a child, three friends, or a grandparent with two grandchildren. For big groups we spread across several canoes by age.</li>
    <li><strong>Mini Sella</strong> adapts to elders' level — 7 km is enough to celebrate the day.</li>
    <li><strong>Everyone sees everyone</strong> at the stops. It is not a solitary activity, it is a shared experience.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="post__pull">
    Family dinners are forgotten. Sella descents with three generations are remembered — and usually end up on someone's living-room wall printed at A3.
  </p>

  <h2 class="post__h2" id="organisation">How we organise <span class="serif-italic">the booking</span></h2>

  <p>Step by step what we ask big groups for:</p>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Exact number of people</strong> — broken down by adults and children (up to 12).</li>
    <li><strong>Specific date</strong> + one alternative.</li>
    <li><strong>Preferred arrival time</strong> — hours are open between 10:30 and 12:30. If you have a preference (more empty river in the morning, more atmosphere at midday), tell us and we will advise.</li>
    <li><strong>Route</strong> — Mini Sella (7 km) or Full route (14.5 km).</li>
    <li><strong>Notes</strong> — pregnancies (excluded), people with special needs, picnic allergies, name of the birthday person or the bride/groom.</li>
    <li><strong>Single contact details</strong> — one person responsible for coordinating with us.</li>
  </ol>

  <p>
    With that we send you a closed quote, payment options (Bizum, transfer, card, payment link) and confirm the booking. For groups of 15+ we ask for <strong>30-50% deposit</strong> to lock the slot, the rest on arrival.
  </p>

  <h2 class="post__h2" id="dates">The <span class="serif-italic">best dates</span> for a group</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>June and September:</strong> the two best months. Mild climate, lively river, fewer crowds, better prices at nearby accommodation.</li>
    <li><strong>July and August:</strong> the classics. More atmosphere at the snack bars, but you need to book ahead (2-3 weeks minimum) and Saturdays fill up.</li>
    <li><strong>May and October:</strong> valid if you go with adults and technical clothing. Less operating but very calm.</li>
    <li><strong>Saturday of the <a href="/en/international-sella-descent/">International Sella Descent</a>:</strong> the Saturday in August set by the Federation (in 2026 · <strong>8 August</strong>). Spectacular plan if the event interests you · that day we offer <strong>a single tourist launch at 12:00</strong> (€35 per person, limited spots, booking up to 2 days before). If you are a large group, plan the date weeks ahead.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Details on flow, crowds and climate by month at <a href="/en/best-time/">the best time of year for the Sella descent</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 class="post__h2" id="price">Group <span class="serif-italic">price</span></h2>

  <p>
    The base rate is the same as individuals: <strong>€30 per child (≤12) and €40 per adult</strong>, all included. See full breakdown at <a href="/en/prices/">Sella descent prices</a>. From 15-20 people we can consider special terms — we do not promise discounts as standard, but we do study it by date, slot and services.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you are after the <strong>top-of-mind plan</strong>, <a href="/en/premium-booking/">Premium Booking</a> reinforces the picnic, adds services and makes a very well-crafted detail for special occasions — ideal for stag/hen parties and round-number birthdays.
  </p>

  <h2 class="post__h2" id="summary">What you need to know <span class="serif-italic">in 6 points</span></h2>

  <ul>
    <li>From <strong>8-10 people</strong> it is handled as a group.</li>
    <li>You can book a <strong>dedicated time slot</strong>, but you cannot "close" the river.</li>
    <li>Base price <strong>€30 kid / €40 adult</strong>, all included.</li>
    <li>Book <strong>2-3 weeks in advance</strong> in August.</li>
    <li>People who do not want to paddle <strong>wait in Arriondas</strong> without trouble.</li>
    <li>For groups <strong>15+ write to us</strong> with date, number and slot for a closed quote.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Have a group in mind and want ideas? <a href="/en/contact/">Write to us</a> with the basics and we will give you a concrete proposal within 24 hours. In August, two weeks ahead is the reasonable minimum — in June or September you have margin.
  </p>
</BlogPostLayout>
